What are ViewResolvers, what is the purpose of them?
ViewResolvers are used for resolving the logical viewname to the View component.
There are basically 5 types of ViewResolvers are there
1. InternalResourceViewResolver = rendering jsp page
2. ResourceBundleViewResolver = supports internationalization
3. BeannameViewResolver = identifies lvn to a bean definition object of a view
4. XmlViewResolver = looks into an xml file to identify the bean definition
5. UrlBasedViewResolver = same as InternalResourceViewResolver, but ViewName is mandatory


